from which it follows that <monospace>Score</monospace>(<italic>y</italic>;<bold>w</bold>)=<bold>w</bold><sup><italic>T</italic></sup><bold>Œ¶</bold>(<italic>y</italic>). We can apply the usual rules for computing subgradients see, e.g. Bertsekas <italic>et al.</italic>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B2">2003</xref>) to obtain
